column5: You don't need it anymore and if you travel by road it's impossible to fillit up
This post was over a year ago ! Things have changed !.......LOL.

My ArriveCan receipt has a V vaccination - please speak with the Canada Border Services Officer on entry to Canada on it. My buddies filled theirs out the same as far as we know and theirs says I on it. What does the difference mean? We had identical vaccination records as far as what vaccine we took and all were months ago. Thanks for your help.
did you by chance have a vasectomy ?

This receipt is proof that you've successfully completed your submission. Your ArriveCAN receipt doesn't provide confirmation that you're eligible to enter Canada or of any public health exemptions, including those for fully vaccinated travellers.You may see a letter identifier beside your name on your receipt. This indicates that you may have to discuss with a public health officer one of the following upon entry:your quarantine plan (Q)your symptom self-assessment (S)If you see an 'I' or a 'V' next to your name, it means that you have indicated in ArriveCAN that you are fully vaccinated.You'll receive a copy of your receipt by email. You must show your ArriveCAN receipt, COVID-19 test results and proof of COVID-19 vaccination (if applicable) to a Canada border services officer upon entry. You can show your receipt by presenting either of the following:the emaila printouta screenshotthrough ArriveCAN directlyIt is about half way down: https://www.canada.ca/en/public-heal...ecan/help.html
I don't think you have to show nothin to get into Fort Knox,so that goes to show you how much those golden walleyes are worth.

Hi, I have completed ArriveCAN the receipt was indicated as V at first. After a couple of minutes, it changes to A (it says: QR Authenticated). I have been vaccinated in Canada and uploaded the proof provided by Provincial Gov. I wanted to know if you have any experience or knowledge on this matter. What does it mean?
What does one do if they don't have a cell phone and has to travel 2 days to get to the border?

good question to contact Canadian customs with. If you are traveling with someone that does have a mobile phone they can list multiple individuals for entry on their ArriveCAN app. I have seen folks in our group list as singles and groups neither had issues.
Sabi, same thing happened to me. What happened at the airport for you? I am boarding tomorrow. TIA

V means your vaccination is was uploaded successfully but unable to be read by OCR I means your vaccination was successfully uploaded and read by OCR A means your vaccination was authenticated by provincial QR code.
Oh that's it, thanks for the explanationfnf
